      conseils: "CDG is the airport you need for intercontinental and long-haul flights, including Air France's worldwide network and all major international carriers. The Francilienne ring road bypasses Paris completely, delivering a smooth and predictable route even when the capital's roads are at their busiest. We recommend allowing at least 3 hours before your flight for a comfortable departure experience, particularly for destinations requiring additional security procedures or documentation. If you have explored Brie-Comte-Robert's castle or rose garden before your trip, your driver will be happy to help with luggage from your accommodation.",
